  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strategic Assistance for Emergency Response in DRC (SAFER) III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Consortium, led by Mercy Corps, working with Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC), ACTED, Solidarit&#xE9;s International (SI), and Concern Worldwide, jointly proposes a new phase of the SAFER programme, to continue to respond to the needs of people affected by conflict and natural disasters in Eastern DRC. The proposed new programme is for a 12 month intervention that will provide packages of support (Multi-sectoral market based (CVA) or in-kind assistance and complementary to specific Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WaSH) ) to 320,847 beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
